	<h2>Strategic Considerations</h2>

	<h3>For Disputers</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>High conviction disputes:</strong> Only worth posting if you're confident you'll win
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Cost escalation:</strong> Later disputes become prohibitively expensive for casual participants
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Fork risk:</strong> High-stakes disputes push toward fork, which affects all markets
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>For Market Users</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Monitor disputes:</strong> Watch the fork meter if your market outcome is disputed
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Expect delays:</strong> Disputed markets settle slower than undisputed ones
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Fork possibility:</strong> High-risk markets might not settle until after a fork
		</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Current Metrics</h2>

	<p>
		The fork meter tracks:
	</p>

	<ul>
		<li>
			<strong>Largest Dispute Bond:</strong> The biggest bond currently active across all markets
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Active Disputes:</strong> How many markets have ongoing disputes
		</li>
		<li>
			<strong>Fork Risk %:</strong> (Largest Bond ÷ 275,000 REP) × 100
		</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		These metrics give you a real-time view of how close Augur is to a fork event.
	</p>

